                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">IMHO charisma is only third check on a charm break...
<br />

<br />
First there is level difference. A mob 10 level lower than you has a lower chance of resisting your charm than a 1 level lower.
<br />

<br />
Second I would say that MR affects charm more (i.e. you tash before you charm, charm breaks often when Tash wears off). If the gap between your MR and the MR of the Mob is bigger, charm is much likely to last longer. I don't know if there is a soft cap.
<br />

<br />
Last and least there is charisma. If you loose your roll on the previous 2 checks, charisma is taken into account.
<br />

<br />
Note that this is my own theory due to my experience with charming and that I fare quite well taking these thoughts into account prior to charm s.th. and I charm in LDoN hard and Ferubi without any problems.
<br />

<br />
As you can see, my charisma is short above 200 unbuffed, but my charm almost always last the complete duration. Just keep GoD and SoM (forget about FoS/Fo7 if you're charming) always up <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=570337" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nillatin</a> Lu`Aras</span>
<br />
Coercer of <a href="http://www.drachentaenzer.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Drachentaenzer</a>
<br />
<span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">Kael Drakkal</span>
