                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That article about the 200 'soft cap' is dated in 2000. Many things have changed since then. I know that way back when, 200 was the soft cap for wis/int, and stats above that gave dimishing returns (although some benefit was gained, be it small)
<br />

<br />
I have since semi-retired my cleric, and my main is now a War, and the 'soft cap' for war sta is 255ish.
<br />

<br />
I realize this is kinda apples to oranges, but, I would bet my bottom dollar that the 'soft cap' for cha benefits has also increased with the advent of the higher 'hards caps' added with PoP.
<br />

<br />
Whether or not cha still factors into charming resist/duration like they described in those articles, I can not say. (the most recent article being from fanfaire Aug 2002)</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
